cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB 

This paper deals with the problem of entity typing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses several machine learning models and techniques, which fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset, which involves mapping Freebase types to WordNet, which is related to knowledge representation and databases, and thus, cs.DB (Databases) is also a possible sub-category.
